ain: memory\n- type: memory_governor\n- title: one-line description of the change\n- summary: brief explanation\n- proposal_path: the .md file path written in Step 7\n- target_system: memory_governor\n- target_ref: same as id\n- risk_level: low (default for memory compaction/additions unless content suggests otherwise)\n- allowed_actions: [\"approve\", \"reject\"]\n- decision_brief:\n    decision: plain-English statement of what is being approved\n    why_proposed: why this change was generated\n    changes_if_approved: list of concrete changes\n    risks: list of risks if any\n    recommended_action: approve | reject | review\n    confidence: low | medium | high\n    source_evidence: [proposal_path]\n\nSubmit using:\npython3 /home/clawbot/.openclaw/scripts/decision_queue_submit.py << 'JSON'\n{ ... }\nJSON\n\nParse the returned JSON. Extract ok, id, discord_card.\n\nIf ok is false: do NOT post a normal notification. Instead post:\n\"⚠️ Decision Queue submission failed for {id}: {error}. Proposal file written to {proposal_path}.\"\n\nIf ok is true: proceed to Step 8 using the returned discord_card as the message body.\n\n## Step 8 -- Deliver to Discord\n\nOutput the discord_card returned by decision_queue_submit.py as your response message.\nOpenClaw delivers it to Discord automatically.\nOne message per successfully submitted proposal item.\n\n## Hard rules\n- One proposal message only\n- Do NOT write to MEMORY.md\n- Do NOT write to any other system\n- Fewer candidates is better than weak candidates\n- If uncertain, discard\n- Silent if nothing passes -- no file, no message\n- Do not post a normal approval notification unless decision_queue_submit.py returns ok=true.\n- Do not ask Leo to approve anything that does not have a Decision Queue ID.\n- Do not use \"approve all\".\n- The .md proposal is evidence. The Decision Queue row is state. Discord is notification only.",
